      • parseProperty

        public java.util.function.Supplier<? extends java.lang.Object> parseProperty​(PropertyBinding propertyBinding,
                                                                             JsonParsingContext parsingContext)
                                                                      throws BindingException,
                                                                             java.io.IOException
        Parses the field and value for the bound property provided by the propertyBinding parameter.

        When called, the parser's current token is expected to be at the VALUE.

        When this method returns, the parser's current token is expected to be at the next JsonToken.FIELD_NAME if there are more fields to parse, or at the JsonToken.END_OBJECT if the last field has been parsed.

        Parameters:
        propertyBinding - the bound property to be parsed
        parsingContext - the configured parsing context
        Returns:
        a supplier that will provide the value
        Throws:
        BindingException - if a binding error occurs whole parsing the target property
        java.io.IOException - if an input error has occurred
